<http://drug.uk/usage/pregnancy/ab1e720e-2bff-47dd-be25-e737c27d8d85> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> " Teratogenic risk in first trimester (trimethoprim a folate antagonist).\nNeonatal haemolysis and methaemoglobinaemia in third trimester; fear of increased risk of kernicterus in neonates appears to be unfounded." .
<http://drug.uk/usage/pregnancy/ab1e720e-2bff-47dd-be25-e737c27d8d85> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/Usage> .
<http://drug.uk/usage/renal-impairment/9d137d78-a9b3-4671-9e1e-09c36218f32a> <http://drug.uk/model/patientCondition> "RenalImpairment" .
<http://drug.uk/usage/renal-impairment/9d137d78-a9b3-4671-9e1e-09c36218f32a> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> " Avoid if creatinine clearance less than 15 mL/minute or in severe insufficiency where plasma-sulfamethoxazole concentration cannot be monitored.\nMonitor plasma-sulfamethoxazole concentrations (consult product literature).\nDose adjustments\nIn adults:\nUse half normal dose if creatinine clearance 15–30 mL/minute.\nIn children:\nUse half normal dose if creatinine clearance 15–30 mL/minute (consult product literature)." .
<http://drug.uk/usage/renal-impairment/9d137d78-a9b3-4671-9e1e-09c36218f32a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/Usage> .
